b'[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](bk11ch19.htm)  [Next](bk11ch21.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n**THE ELEVENTH BOOK**\n\n\n\n**Chapter XX**\n\n\n\n**On the description of Brahm a Yaj\xc3\xb1a, Sandhyas, etc.** ****\n\n\n\np. 1116\n\n\n\n1-25. The twice born (Brahma _n_ a) is firstly to sip three times (make\n\xc3\x82chamana); then to make the marjana (sprinkle water) twice; he is to touch the\nwater by the right hand and sprinkle water on his two feet. Next, he is to\nsprinkle with water his head, eyes, nose, ears, heart, and head thoroughly.\nThen speaking out the Des\xc2\x92a and Kala (place and time) he should commence the\nBrahma Yaj\xc3\xb1a. Next for the destruction of all the sins and for getting\nliberation, he should have the Darbha (sacrificial grass, and the Kus\xc2\x92a\ngrasses), two on his right hand, three on his left hand, one grass each on his\nseat, sacrificial thread, his tuft, and his heels. No sin can now remain in\nhis body.\n\n\n\n\xc2\x93I am performing this Brahma Yaj\xc3\xb1a for the satisfaction of the Devata\naccording to the Sutra,\xc2\x94 thus thinking he is to repeat the Gayatri thrice.\nThen he is to recite the following mantras :-- \xc2\x93Agnimile purohitam, etc.,\xc2\x94\n\xc2\x93Yadamgeti\xc2\x94 \xc2\x93Agnirvai,\xc2\x94 \xc2\x93Mahavratanchaiva pantha,\xc2\x94 \xc2\x93Athata _h_ S\xc2\x92amhitayas\xc2\x92cha\nvidamaghavat,\xc2\x94 \xc2\x93Mahavratasya,\xc2\x94 \xc2\x93\xc3\x8e _s_ etvorjetva,\xc2\x94 \xc2\x93Agna ayahi\xc2\x94 \xc2\x93S\xc2\x92anno Devi\nrabbis _t_ aye,\xc2\x94 \xc2\x93Tasya Samamnayo\xc2\x94 \xc2\x93Briddairadaich\xc2\x94 \xc2\x93S\xc2\x92ik _s_ am pravak _s_\nyami,\xc2\x94 \xc2\x93Pa _n_ cha Samvatsareti,\xc2\x94 \xc2\x93Mayarasatajabhetyeva,\xc2\x94 \xc2\x93Gaurgma,\xc2\x94 also he\nis to recite the two following Sutras :-- \xc2\x93Athato Dharma Jij\xc3\xb1asa,\xc2\x94 \xc2\x93Athato\nBrahma Jij\xc3\xb1asa.\xc2\x94 Next he is to recite the mantra \xc2\x93Tachhamyo _h_ \xc2\x94 and also the\nmantra \xc2\x93Namo Brahma _n_ e namo stvagnaye nama _h_ prithivyai nama Osadhibhyo\n_h_ nama _h_ \xc2\x94. (These mantras are the famous mantras of the Rig Veda). Next\nperform the Deva-tarpa _n_ am, thus :-- \xc2\x93Om Prajapati stripyatu\xc2\x94, \xc2\x93Om Brahma\nstripyatu\xc2\x94, \xc2\x93Om Vedas tripyantu,\xc2\x94 \xc2\x93Om Ri _s_ ayastri pyantu\xc2\x94, \xc2\x93 Om\nDevastripantu,\xc2\x94 \xc2\x93Om Sarva _n_ i chhandamsi tripyantu\xc2\x94, \xc2\x93Om Om Kara stripyatu\xc2\x94,\n\xc2\x93Om Va _s_ a _t_ Kara stripyatu\xc2\x94, \xc2\x93Om Vyarhitayas tripyantu\xc2\x94, Om Savitri\ntripyatu\xc2\x94, \xc2\x93Om Gayatri tripyatu\xc2\x94, \xc2\x93Om Yaj\xc3\xb1a stripyantu,\xc2\x94 Om Dyava prithivyau\ntripyatam. Om antarik _s_ am tripyatu, Om Ahoratrani tripyantu, Om Samkkya\nstripyantu, Om Siddha stripyantu, Om Samudra stripyantu, Om Nadyas tripyantu,\nOm girayas tripyantu, Om Ksettrau _s_ adhivana spati gandharva Psarasas\ntripyantu, Om naga vayamsi gavascha sadhya viprasta thaiva cha, yak _s_ a rak\n_s_ a _n_ si bhutani tyeva mantani tripyantu. Next, suspending the sacrificial\nthread from the neck, perform the Ri _s_ i tarpa _n_ am, thus :-- Om\nS\xc2\x92atarchinas tripyantu, Om madhyamas tripyantu,\n\n\n\np. 1117\n\n\n\nOm Gritsamada stripyatu, Om Vis\xc2\x92vamitra stripyantu, Om Vamadeva stripyantu, Om\nAtri stripyatu, Om Bharadvajastripyatu, Om Vas\xc2\x92i _st_ hastripyatu, Om\nPragathastripyatu, Pavamanyastripyantu. Next, holding the sacrificial thread\nover the right shoulder and under the left arm, perform the Tarpa _n_ am, thus\n:--\n\n\n\nOm K _s_ udrasukta stripyantu.\n\nOm Mahasuktastripyantu.\n\nOm Sanaka stripyatu.\n\nOm Sananda stripyatu.\n\nOm Sanatana stripyatu.\n\nOm Sanat Kumara stripyatu.\n\nOm Kapila stripyatu.\n\nOm \xc3\x82suristripyatu,\n\nOm Vohalistripyatu.\n\nOm Pa\xc3\xb1chas\xc2\x92ikha stripyatu.\n\nOm Sumantu Jaimini Vais\xc2\x92ampayana Paila Sutra Bha _s_ ya bharata Maha Bharata\nDharmacharyah stripyantu.\n\nOm Janantivaha vigargya Gautama S\xc2\x92akalya vabhravya Mandavya Mandukeya\nstripyantu.\n\nOm Gargi Vachak _n_ avi tripyatu.\n\nOm Vadava pratitheyi tripyatu.\n\nOm Sulabha maitreyi tripyatu.\n\nOm Kahola stripyatu.\n\nOm Kau _s_ itaka stripyatu.\n\nOm Maha Kau _s_ itaka stripyatu.\n\nOm Bharadvaja stripyatu,\n\nOm Paimga stripyatu.\n\nOm Mahapaimga stripyatu.\n\nOm Sujaj\xc3\xb1a stripyatu.\n\nOm Samkhyayana stripyatu.\n\nOm Aitareya stripyatu.\n\nOm Mahaitareya stripyatu.\n\nOm Vaskala stripyatu.\n\nOm Sakala stripyatu.\n\nOm Sujata vaktra stripyatu.\n\nOm Audavahi stripyatu.\n\nOm Saujami stripyatu,\n\nOm S\xc2\x92aunaka stripyatu,\n\nOm \xc3\x82s\xc2\x92valayana stripyatu.\n\n\n\np. 1118\n\n\n\n26-54. Let all the other \xc3\x82charyas be satisfied. \xc2\x93Om Ye Ke chasma _t_ kule Jata\naputra gotri _n_ o mritah. te grih _n_ antu maya dattam vastrani _s_ pi _d_ i\nto dakam.\xc2\x94 Saying thus offer water squeezed out of a cloth. O Narada! Thus I\nhave spoken to you of the rules of Brahma Yaj\xc3\xb1a. Whoever performs thus the\nBrahma Yaj\xc3\xb1a gets the fruits of studying all the Vedas. Then performing, in\ndue order, the Vais\xc2\x92va deva, Homa, S\xc2\x92raddha, serving the guests, and feeding\nthe cows, the devotee is to take his meals during the fifth part of the day\nalong with the other Brahma _n_ as. Then the sixth and the seventh parts of\nthe day he is to spend in reading histories and the Pura _n_ as. Then the\neighth part of the day he is to devote in seeing the relatives, talking with\nthem and receiving visits from other persons; then he will be prepared to\nperform the evening Sandhya. O Narada! I am now talking of the evening\nSandhya. Listen. S\xc2\x92ri Bhagavati is pleased very quickly with him who performs\nthe evening Sandhya. First make the \xc3\x82chaman and make the Vayu (air) in the\nbody steady. With heart tranquilled and with the seat Baddha Padmasana, be\ncalm and quiet while engaged in performing the Sandhya. At the commencement of\nall actions prescribed in the S\xc2\x92rutis and Smritis, first perform the Sagarbha\nPra _n_ ayama. In other words recite the mantra mentally for the due number of\nmoments and make the Pranayama. Simply meditating is called Agarbha Pra _n_\nayama. Here no mantra is necessary to be recited. Then have the Bhutas\xc2\x92uddhi\n(have the purifications of the elements) and make the Sankalpa. First of all,\nthe purification of elements, etc., are to be done first; one becomes, then,\nentitled to do other actions. While doing Puraka (inhaling), Kumbhaka\n(retaining) and Rechaka (exhaling) in Pra _n_ ayama, meditate on the Deity\nstated duly. In the evening time meditate on the Bhagavati Sandhya Devi thus\n:-- The name of the then Gayatri Devi is Sarasvati. She is old, of black\ncolour, wearing ordinary clothes; in her hands are seen conch shell, disc,\nclub and lotus. On Her feet the anklets are making sweet tinkling sounds; on\nHer loins there is the golden thread; decked with various ornaments. She is\nsitting on Garu _d_ a. On Her head the invaluable jewel crown is seen; on Her\nneck, the necklaces of stars; Her forehead is shining with a brilliant lustre\nemitting from the pearl and jewel Tatamka ornaments. She has put on yellow\nclothes; Her nature is eternal knowledge and ever-bliss. She is uttering Sama\nVeda. She resides in the Heavens and daily She goes in the path of the Sun. I\ninvoke the Devi from the Solar Orb. O Narada! Meditate on the Devi thus and\nperform the Sandhya. Then perform the Marjanam by the mantra \xc2\x93\xc3\x82pohi _st_ ha\xc2\x94\nand next by the mantra\n\n\n\np. 1119\n\n\n\n\xc2\x93Agnis\xc2\x92cha ma manyus\xc2\x92cha.\xc2\x94 The remaining actions are the same as before. Next,\nrepeat the Gayatri and offer, with a pure heart, the offering of Arghya to the\nSun for the satisfaction of Naraya _n_ a. While offering this Arghya, keep the\ntwo legs level and similar and take water in folded palms and meditating on\nthe Devata within the Solar Orb, throw it towards Him. The fool that offers\nSuryarghya in the water, out of ignorance, disregarding the injunctions of the\nS\xc2\x92rutis, will have to perform Prayas\xc2\x92chitta for that sin. Next, worship the\nSun by the Surya mantra. Then taking one\xc2\x92s seat, meditate on the Devi and\nrepeat the Gayatri. One thousand times or five hundred times the Gayatri is to\nbe repeated. The worship, etc., in the evening is the same as in the morning.\nNow I am speaking of the Tarpa _n_ am in the Evening Sandhya. Hear. Vas\xc2\x92i _st_\nha is the Ri _s_ i of the aforesaid Sarasvati. Vi _sn_ u in the form of\nSarasvati is the Devata; Gayatri is the Chhanda; its application is in the\nEvening Sandhya Tarpa _n_ am. Now the Tarpa _n_ am of the Sandhyanga (the\nadjunct of Sandhya) runs as follows :--\n\n\n\n\xc2\x93Om Sva _h_ Puru _s_ am Tarpayami.\xc2\x94\n\n\xc2\x93Om Samavedam Tarpayami.\xc2\x94\n\n\xc2\x93Om Suryama _nd_ alam tarpayami.\xc2\x94\n\n\xc2\x93Om Hira _n_ yagarbham tarpayami.\xc2\x94\n\n\xc2\x93Om Paramatmanam tarpayami.\xc2\x94\n\n\xc2\x93Om Sarasvatim tarpayami.\xc2\x94\n\n\xc2\x93Om Devamataram tarpayami.\xc2\x94\n\n\xc2\x93Om Samkritim tarpayami.\xc2\x94\n\n\xc2\x93Om Vriddham Sandhyam tarpayami\n\n\xc2\x93Om Vi _sn_ u rupinim Usasim tarpayami.\xc2\x94\n\n\xc2\x93Om Nirmrijim tarpayami.\xc2\x94\n\n\xc2\x93Om Sarvasiddhi kari _n_ im tarpayami.\xc2\x94\n\n\xc2\x93Om Sarvamantra dhipatikam tarpayami.\xc2\x94\n\n\xc2\x93Om Bhurbhuva _h_ Sva _h_ Puru _s_ am tarpayami.\xc2\x94\n\n\n\nThus perform the Vaidik Tarpa _n_ am. O Narada! Thus have been described the\nrules of the sin destroying evening Sandhya. By this evening Sandhya, all\nsorts of pains and afflictions and diseases are removed. And ultimately the\nMok _s_ a is obtained. What more than this that you should know this Sandhya\nBanda _n_ am as the principal thing amongst the good conduct and right ways of\nliving. Therefore S\xc2\x92ri Bhagavati fructifies all the desires of the Bhaktas who\nperform this Sandhya Vanda _n_ am.\n\n\n\np. 1120\n\n\n\nHere ends the Twentieth Chapter of the Eleventh Book on the description of\nBrahma Yaj\xc3\xb1a, Sandhyas, etc., in the Mahapura _n_ am S\xc2\x92ri Mad Devi Bhagavatam\nof 18,000 verses by Mahar _s_ i Veda Vyasa.\n\n\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: Chapter 21](bk11ch21.htm)\n\n'